title: Why Kim Jong Un wants you to meet his daughter
description: With his young daughter at this side at two splashy military events this week, Kim Jong Un told the world two things -- the Kim family will rule North Korea for another generation and it will have the nuclear weapons to make sure no one can challenge that.

title: NASA rover finds 'clearest evidence yet' of an ancient lake on Mars
description: In the foothills of a Martian mountain, NASA's Curiosity rover found stunning new evidence of an ancient lake in the form of rocks etched with the ripples of waves — and the telltale signs appeared in an unlikely place.

title: Retired colonel on what he believes 'high-altitude object' in Alaska could be
description: Retired US Air Force Col. Cedric Leighton shares what he believes to be different between the "high-altitude object" that was shot down in Alaska and the suspected Chinese spy balloon.

title: US: We don't know if it's a balloon or who it belongs to
We don't know if it's a balloon or who it belongs to, US says
Watch how many times Gordon Ramsay spits out food while judging Super Bowl snacks
description: Gordon Ramsay joins James Corden to judge homemade Super Bowl snacks prepared by "The Late Late Show" staff. The "Super Bowl Snackdown" segment leads to the celebrity chef spitting out almost everything he tried.

title: White House on what we know about 'high-altitude object' so far
description: The White House says that President Joe Biden ordered the military to down what it described as a "high-altitude object" hovering over Alaska. Hear the National Security Council coordinator for strategic communications John Kirby explain.

title: New Zealand braces for its most intense tropical cyclone since the 1990s
description: New Zealand is bracing for its most intense tropical cyclone since the 1990s. Tropical Cyclone Gabrielle is heading toward the North Island just two weeks after the area was hit with record flooding.

title: Biden ordered US military to 'down' a 'high-altitude object' over Alaska, White House says
description: The White House announced Friday that President Joe Biden ordered the military to down what it described as a "high-altitude object" hovering over Alaska earlier in the day.

title: Spain will offer citizenship to freed political prisoners from Nicaragua
description: Spain will offer a path to citizenship for 222 Nicaraguan political prisoners who were recently released from prison and many of whom were sent to the United States on Thursday, a spokesman for Spain's Ministry of Foreign Affairs told CNN.

title: Tiger Woods announces return to competitive golf at The Genesis Invitational next week
description: Tiger Woods announced Friday a return to competitive golf at next week's The Genesis Invitational, a tournament he hosts.

title: Biden to visit Poland around Ukraine war anniversary
description: President Joe Biden will visit Poland this month to mark the one-year anniversary of Russia's invasion of Ukraine, returning to the region as the war enters a volatile new phase without a clear path to peace.

title: The last surviving Blockbuster has an ad timed for the Super Bowl
description: When you're the last lone surviving store in any industry, you've earned the right to have fun and hype it up. That's exactly what the only remaining store of the Blockbuster video rental chain is doing, and it's during the Super Bowl. And it helps if you still have a VCR, of course.

title: Eat less to live longer, study says, but are the tools measuring longevity accurate?
description: People of normal weight may be able to extend their life span by restricting calories, according to a new study that attempted to measure the pace of aging in people asked to cut their calorie intake by 25% over two years.

title: Exclusive: US developed method to track China's spy balloon fleet within last year, sources say
description: The US intelligence community has developed a method to track China's fleet of surveillance balloons that was only discovered within the last year, six people familiar with the matter tell CNN.

title: Spanish teenage cyclist dies after being hit by truck during training
description: Teenage cyclist Estela Domínguez has died after being hit by a truck while training, the Royal Spanish Cycling Federation (RFEC) said in a statement on Friday.

title: Lula calls Bolsonaro a 'faithful copycat of Trump'
description: Brazilian President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva said the divisions in his country were no worse than the political split in the United States, in an exclusive CNN interview Friday ahead of his meeting with President Joe Biden at the White House.

title: White House says Biden's Super Bowl interview with Fox is off
description: A last-ditch effort to salvage a Fox interview with President Joe Biden before the Super Bowl has fallen through.

title: Abe exposes Trump's thought process ahead of US-North Korea summit in posthumous memoir
description: Former Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe urged then-President Donald Trump not to relent with North Korea and to keep up the threat of military pressure, according to his memoir.

title: Handful of 'miracle' rescues, but hopes dim
What the US knows about China's spy balloon thus far
description: As tensions between the US and China escalate after the US shot down and recovered a suspected spy balloon, CNN's Will Ripley looks at the claims made by the respective countries, details surrounding the balloon, and China's vast military surveillance program.

title: Woman describes losing family in devastating earthquake
description: Salma Salazar lost her sister, brother-in-law, and two nephews in the 7.8 magnitude earthquake that struck Turkey. More than 22,000 people have been killed and tens of thousands injured in Turkey and Syria, officials say.

title: Amanpour to Lula: How do you deal with half your population despising you?
description: In an exclusive interview, Brazilian President Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva speaks to CNN's Christiane Amanpour ahead of his meeting with US President Joe Biden at the White House.

title: Burt Bacharach: Songs you may not know he wrote
description: Burt Bacharach has one of the most impressive songbooks in the history of the music industry.

title: A juicy new book explores the cultural history of the backside
description: In the introduction to her book "Butts: A Backstory," journalist Heather Radke recalls a moment when, at 10 years old, she and a friend were cat-called by two teenage boys while out riding their bikes.

title: Cockatoos can not only use tools, they can carry whole toolkits to trickier jobs, study shows
description: The ability to solve problems with multiple tools is a rare talent in the animal kingdom, but according to new research, cockatoos are the first birds on the block to carry and use a tool kit to suit their needs.

title: Long-term exposure to air pollution may raise risk of depression later in life, study says
description: Exposure to air pollution may be tied to the risk of developing depression later in life, a large new study finds.

title: Black history observance began as a single week. It's time for a full season
description: Nearly 50 years ago, political leaders thought Black history was so important to the national identity that they quadrupled the time formally set aside for it.

title: Must-watch videos of the week
Watch SpaceX fire 31 engines on the most powerful rocket ever
description: SpaceX completed what it says was a successful test after 31 of the 33 Raptor engines on its Starship rocket fired during a statis test. Starship is what SpaceX hopes to use to one day send humans to Mars.

title: Rihanna shares what made her want to perform at this year's Super Bowl

title: SEC targets 'crypto-staking' in $30 million Kraken settlement
description: The Securities and Exchange Commission has reached a $30 million settlement with the cryptocurrency platform Kraken that will force it to unwind a program offering investment returns to US users who committed their digital assets to the company.

title: Florida senator invoked Jake Tapper 8 times in a 10-minute interview. Hear Tapper's response
description: Sen. Rick Scott (R-FL) defended his proposal to sunset all federal legislation after five years, including medicare and social security, by comparing it to a 2017 Republican healthcare plan to cut costs, and repeatedly cited a 2017 interview by CNN anchor Jake Tapper during his defense. Tapper responds on CNN's This Morning.

title: Here are low-impact exercises that may ease your arthritis pain
description: Feeling lucky that you don't have arthritis? Don't celebrate just yet. Nearly one-quarter of adults in the United States has arthritis, or about 58.5 million people, according to the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

title: Arrest made in the death of a 'beloved' New Jersey kindergarten teacher found buried in a shallow grave, prosecutors say
description: An arrest has been made in the death of a New Jersey kindergarten teacher found buried in a shallow grave, prosecutors said.

title: Scientists fear a Great Toxic Dustbowl could soon emerge from the Great Salt Lake
description: Like the rest of the West, Utah has a water problem. But megadrought and overconsumption aren't just threats to wildlife, agriculture and industry here. A disappearing Great Salt Lake could poison the lungs of more than 2.5 million people.

title: Two dead including child as car rams people at Jerusalem bus stop
description: A car drove into people at a bus stop in Jerusalem Friday, killing at least two including a child in what Israeli police are initially describing as a "ramming terror attack."

title: After years away from the spotlight, Phoebe Philo is launching her new fashion label in September
description: When British designer Phoebe Philo announced she was stepping down from the top creative job at luxury fashion house Celine in 2017, women around the world took a sharp, collective in-take of breath.

description: A devastating earthquake in southern Turkey could change the electoral equation for Turkish strongman President Recep Tayyip Erdogan, who hopes an upcoming election will extend his rule well into a third decade.

description: This op-ed contains spoilers for "The Last of Us."

description: When Brazil's new president, Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva, meets President Joe Biden at the White House on Friday, the two hope to reset relations after an era defined by right-wing populists and threats to democracy in both nations.

title: Electric buses are driving a silent revolution in Nairobi

To curb the transmission of the virus, authorities called on the city's thousands of private bus operators to cease trading. "Within three days, the air completely cleared," recalls entrepreneur Jit Bhattacharya. "You could see Mount Kenya ... crystal clear," some 90 miles away.

From Loewe's Spring-Summer 2023 Minnie Mouse stilettos (which have already received the Kylie Jenner seal of approval) to Balenciaga's Hummer Derby clown-like loafers, playful footwear appears to be on the rise. This week, another pair of shoes has entered the chat: The Big Red Boot.
